CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 27, 1957, pg. 2, reads: "What! Again? - For the second time within a week, the rear walls of a house fell on Charles St. Monday. First wall, which is being repaired is shown to the right of the partition. Second wall, which fell Monday, is missing and is piled up in brick, plaster and rubble below as bathroom and kitchen of house next door are exposed. Police fear front walls may fall, also. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Two story row houses with collapsed exterior wall exposing bathroom and kitchen sink, 2500 block of Charles Street, Northside
